'''Algiers''' is an [[unincorporated community]] in [[Jefferson Township, Pike County, Indiana|Jefferson Township]], [[Pike County, Indiana|Pike County]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Indiana]].<ref>{{cite gnis|430075|Algiers, Indiana|2017-02-06}}</ref>

==History==
Algiers was laid out in 1868.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4uIKAwAAQBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=PA355#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=History of Pike and Dubois Counties, Indiana | author=Goodspeed Brothers | pages=355}}</ref> The community was named after [[Algiers]], the capital of Algeria.<ref>{{cite book|last=Baker|first=Ronald L.|title=From Needmore to Prosperity: Hoosier Place Names in Folklore and History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SXB5AAAAMAAJ|date=October 1995|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=978-0-253-32866-3|page=48|quote=...apparently for the city in North Africa...}}</ref> An old variant name of the community was called Delectible.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://geonames.usgs.gov/apex/f?p=138:4:0::NO:4:P4_FID,P4_OBJECTID,P4_FNAME:430075,31625121,Delectible|title=USGS detail on Algiers - Variant Citation|accessdate=2017-02-06}}</ref> 

A post office called Algiers was established in 1885, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1955.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.postalhistory.com/postoffices.asp?task=display&state=IN&county=Pike | title=Pike County | publisher=Jim Forte Postal History | accessdate=5 October 2015}}</ref>

The town's name is part of the namesake of the [[Algers, Winslow and Western Railway]] which operates within Pike County.

==Geography==
Algiers is located at {{coord|38|29|14|N|87|10|30|W|type:city}}.

